<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5775724>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. A–C. Dorsal, ventral, and lateral view of preserved Schismaderma branchi sp. nov. paratype female (PEMA14246). Photographs by W.R. Branch." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5775724/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5775728>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Preserved tadpole of Schismaderma branchi sp. nov. (PEM A14307). A–C. Lateral, dorsal, and ventral view. D. Oral disc with LRTF of 2/3 (posterior 3rd low above 2nd row, not captured in photograph). Photographs by N.L. Baptista (A–C), W. Conradie (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5775728/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5775722>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Schismaderma branchi sp. nov. holotype (ZMB 91630). A. Dorsal surface, showing adult coloration, particularly the absence of obvious dorsal paired sacral dark blotches and presence of lateral dark stripe. B. Ventral surface showing characteristic white ground colour and heavily semi-reticulate, dark blotches on ventrum, throat and limbs. C. Lateral shot of head. D. Left hand. E. Left foot. Photographs by N.L. Baptista." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5775722/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5775726>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Ventral surface and tuberculation of left hand and feet in Schismaderma. A–B. S. carens, adult male (PEM A10766). C–D. S. carens, adult male (PEM A2523). E–F. S. branchi sp. nov. paratype, adult female (PEM A14246). G–H. S. branchi sp. nov. holotype, adult male (ZMB 91630). Photographs by W.R. Branch (A–D) and N.L. Baptista (E–H)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5775726/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5775716>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Life colour of Schimaderma carens, showing typical pattern with dorsum varying from bright red to orange-grey and mid-dorsal dark spots usually present. All photographs by Louis Du Preez." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5775716/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5775733>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Photographs of live individuals of Schismaderma branchi sp. nov. A. Live adult female paratype (PEM A14246) B. Mating ball. C. Pair in amplexus. D. Female and recently laid eggs. E. Egg strings. F. Habitat and tadpoles in schools. Photographs A–D, F by P. Vaz Pinto; photograph E by K. Luchansky." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5775733/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5775730>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Oscillogram and sonogram of advertisement calls of: A. Schismaderma carens. B. Schismaderma branchi sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5775730/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5775712>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Map of sub-Saharan Africa with the known distribution of Schismaderma carens, and localities of S. branchi sp. nov. (pink circles) and S. carens specimens analysed morphologically (blue triangles) and genetically (red circles). Map adapted from IUCN (2020) and compiled by L. Veríssimo." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5775712/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

